<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1474917 size-full" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=640%2C427&#038;ssl=1" alt="Police shoot 4 suspected bandits, recover 2 motorcycles, weapon in Niger" width="640" height="427" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?w=640&amp;ssl=1 640w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=58%2C39&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=260%2C173&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=195%2C130&amp;ssl=1 195w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=115%2C77&amp;ssl=1 115w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Police Command in Niger said its operatives in collaboration with a local vigilance group have shot four suspected bandits in Mashegu Local Government Area of the state. The Commissioner of Police in the state, Mr Adamu Usman, made this known in an interview with News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Minna on Thursday. Usman said on Nov.11 at about 005 hours, a joint Police/Vigilance group on clearance operation encountered bandits in a bush that stretched from Baban Lamba via Kontagora village in Mashegu local government area. He explained that in process one vigilance operative, Auwalu Laura, was shot on his leg and was rushed to General Hospital, Kontagora for treatment. However, two unregistered boxer motorcycles with bloodstains, one AK 47 rifle, one live ammunition abandoned by the fleeting bandits were recovered at the scene of the operation. The commissioner said that four of the suspected bandits were arrested with gunshot wounds, but that they died while being conveyed to the hospital for treatment. “ Their corpses have been deposited at the General Hospital, Kontagora, and the case is under investigation,” he said. NAN Vanguard News Nigeria Niger State Police Command has arrested nine suspected kidnappers and rescued sixteen victims from across the state. May 11, 2019 In "News" Another attack on Mashegu Local Government Area of Niger State, yesterday, claimed one life with many injured. The attack is coming on the heels of a similar one on Gurmana, old Gurmana, and Ashirika communities in Shiroro Local Government Area of the state, Saturday, where two were killed. February 10, 2020 In "News" The Inspector-General of Police (IGP), Alhaji Mohammed Adamu, has urged traditional rulers to support the fight against armed robbery, banditry, kidnapping and cattle rustling. September 2, 2020 In "News"